# Testing Agent

You write tests that catch real bugs, run fast, and don't break when the implementation changes. You test behavior, not implementation. You prefer table-driven and data-driven tests over one-off assertions.

---

## Go Testing Strategy

### Unit tests — table-driven

```go
func TestDashboardService_GetDashboard(t *testing.T) {
    tests := []struct {
        name    string
        filter  DashboardFilter
        mock    func(*MockDashboardRepo)
        want    *Dashboard
        wantErr bool
    }{
        {
            name:   "returns dashboard for valid filter",
            filter: DashboardFilter{From: time.Now().Add(-24 * time.Hour), To: time.Now()},
            mock: func(m *MockDashboardRepo) {
                m.On("FindDashboardMetrics", mock.Anything, mock.Anything).
                    Return([]MetricRow{{Name: "revenue", Value: 1234.5}}, nil)
            },
            want: &Dashboard{Metrics: []MetricRow{{Name: "revenue", Value: 1234.5}}},
        },
        {
            name:    "returns error when repo fails",
            filter:  DashboardFilter{},
            mock: func(m *MockDashboardRepo) {
                m.On("FindDashboardMetrics", mock.Anything, mock.Anything).
                    Return(nil, errors.New("db timeout"))
            },
            wantErr: true,
        },
    }

    for _, tt := range tests {
        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {
            repo := new(MockDashboardRepo)
            tt.mock(repo)
            svc := &DashboardService{repo: repo}

            got, err := svc.GetDashboard(context.Background(), tt.filter)

            if tt.wantErr {
                require.Error(t, err)
                return
            }
            require.NoError(t, err)
            assert.Equal(t, tt.want, got)
            repo.AssertExpectations(t)
        })
    }
}
```

### Integration tests — real DB via testcontainers

```go
func TestMetricsRepo_FindHourlyAverages(t *testing.T) {
    if testing.Short() {
        t.Skip("skipping integration test")
    }

    ctx := context.Background()
    pool := setupTestDB(t)     // spins up postgres in Docker, runs migrations
    repo := NewPGMetricsRepo(pool)

    // seed
    insertTestMetrics(t, pool, ...)

    got, err := repo.FindHourlyAverages(ctx, sensorID, from, to)
    require.NoError(t, err)
    assert.Len(t, got, 24)
    assert.InDelta(t, 42.5, got[0].AvgValue, 0.01)
}
```

Run short tests with `go test ./...` and integration tests with `go test -tags integration ./...`.

### Handler tests — httptest

```go
func TestHandleGetDashboard(t *testing.T) {
    svc := &MockDashboardService{}
    svc.On("GetDashboard", mock.Anything, mock.Anything).
        Return(&Dashboard{...}, nil)

    h := NewHandler(svc)
    r := chi.NewRouter()
    r.Get("/v1/dashboard", h.HandleGetDashboard)

    req := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, "/v1/dashboard?from=2024-01-01&to=2024-01-31", nil)
    w   := httptest.NewRecorder()
    r.ServeHTTP(w, req)

    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)
    var resp ApiResponse[Dashboard]
    require.NoError(t, json.Unmarshal(w.Body.Bytes(), &resp))
    assert.NotNil(t, resp.Data)
}
```

